<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000003#     2#         4216#">Va. Code Ann. § 3.2-4216</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_3.2-4216"/><heading><desig>§ 3.2-4216.</desig><title>Recovery of costs and fees by Attorney General</title></heading><bodyText><p>In any action brought by the Commonwealth to enforce this article or Article 1 (<citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 3.2-4200"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 3.2-4200">§ 3.2-4200<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000003#     2#         4200#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> et seq.) of this chapter in which the Commonwealth prevails, or as part of the settlement of any matter arising from an investigation prior to the filing of such action, and in addition to any civil or criminal penalty or other amount which the court may determine, the Attorney General shall be entitled to recover the reasonable costs of investigation, expert witness fees, costs of the action and reasonable attorneys' fees.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="2003 VA CH 798"><content><span normalizedCite="2003 Va. Ch. 798">2003, c. 798<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2003#000798#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, § 3.1-336.14; <citation normalizedCite="2008 VA CH 860"><content><span no